👉 Prisma is an ORM (Object Relational Mapper)
Write code → Prisma converts it → SQL queries → Database
Without prisma: 
SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = 'ch';
with prisma:
prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { username: "ch" }
})

What Prisma does: 
Connects to database
Generates queries
Handles migrations
Type-safe (in TypeScript)

Majorly used with node.js,ts
similar - SQLAlchemy 

