PostgresSql 

It is a database in which data is stored in tables format 
Users table:
id | username | password

Postgres uses sql lang.
Eg:
INSERT INTO Users(username,password):
Values("chihnitha","hash_passwrd")

PostgreSQL → structured, relational, strict
It has tables(rows,column), Relationships (Users → Orders → Payments)



Use PostgreSQL when:

✔ Banking systems
✔ E-commerce (orders, payments)
✔ Authentication systems (like yours)
✔ Analytics & reporting
✔ Complex joins needed

👉 Example:

Amazon
Uber (core systems)

____________________________________________________________________________________________________
MongoDB (NoSQL DB)

It is a database in which data is stored in JSON format 
JSon:
{
  "username": "ch",
  "password": "hashed",
  "orders": [
    {"item": "apple", "price": 10}
  ]
}

- no joins like sql 

MongoDB → flexible, document-based, dynamic


🍃 Use MongoDB when:

✔ Rapid prototyping
✔ JSON-heavy apps
✔ Logs / analytics
✔ Content management
✔ Real-time apps

👉 Example:

Chat apps
IoT data


can use both :
PostgreSQL → core data
MongoDB → logs / flexible data

